The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                               The City Diary
                nSurgeries at SSKM Hospital will be hit for the next few days as part of the hospitals main operating theatre (OT) complex will remain shut, officials said on Tuesday. On Monday, during a routine check, some bacteria were detected in the general surgery OT complex, prompting the authorities to take up a sterilisation drive. However, emergency surgeries will be carried out.    nThe final hearing of the Rizwanur Rahman death case resumed on Tuesday before Justice Dipankar Dutta of Calcutta High Court. The lawyers appearing for the Todis  Pradip Ghosh and Jaymalya Bagchi  challenged the validity of the CBI investigation into the death. The hearing will continue on Wednesday.    nThirteen passengers were injured after an SBSTC bus hit a private bus on the northern slope of Majherhat bridge on Tuesday morning. Ten passengers were rushed to CMRI, while the rest were admitted to SSKM Hospital. The two drivers were arrested and the vehicles seized.    nThe CBSE Class X practical examinations for external candidates will be held on March 27, according to the original schedule, officials of CBSE schools in the city said on Tuesday.    nDhiren Dutta, 65, was critically injured after being hit by a taxi on Aurobindo Setu on Monday night.                                                                                                                                                                   
